            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add 2/3 of the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion </strong>(save the rest for garnish!), the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>wilted spinach</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the garlic has softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> remaining honey </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> with the <strong>reserved starchy noodle water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
